    "description": "Role Summary: Responsible for designing and developing responsive user interfaces that provide a seamless experience across various devices; collaborates with backend team to ensure smooth integration.\nKey Responsibilities: - Design and implement frontend components following UX principles to enhance the overall product interface using html, css, JavaScript (JS), React JS libraries or frameworks such as Angular, Ember.js, Vue Router/Router Mode; ensures consistency in design standards throughout projects. - Conduct user testing sessions for feedback on usability and gather requirements from stakeholders to adapt UI designs accordingly.; works closely with the frontend team to resolve any cross-browser compatibility issues that may arise during development.\nRequired Qualifications: Experience of 3-5 years as a Front-End Developer, preferably in a dynamic web application project environment; knowledge and proficiency in modern JavaScript frameworks/libraries like React JS or Vue Router.; strong understanding of responsive design principles to ensure interfaces are compatible with different devices and screen sizes.",
